---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Why the 48-Team Format is a Massive W" description="Forget the boomers crying about tradition. More teams means more chaotic underdog energy.">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4 bg-[#f9a8d4]">
    <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl bg-white border-[4px] border-black p-8 md:p-12 shadow-[12px_12px_0px_#000] relative z-20">
      <div class="inline-block bg-yellow-300 text-black border-[3px] border-black font-black px-4 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">FORMAT UPDATES</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-6 leading-none" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;">
        Why the 48-Team Format is Actually a Massive W
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-black font-medium leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-black border-l-8 border-l-pink-500">
          Football purists are literally crying, throwing up, and sliding down the wall right now. But let's be real—the 2026 format change from 32 to 48 teams is exactly what the sport needs. 
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;">1. The Underdog Energy Will Be Unmatched</h2>
        <p>
          We all saw what Morocco did in 2022, right? The global south is finally getting the representation it deserves. Africa went from 5 slots to 9. Asia went from 4.5 to 8. We are going to see teams that have literally never played on the global stage completely disrupt the established European powerhouses. If you don't think a random debutant nation parking the bus and taking Germany to penalties isn't pure cinema, you don't know ball.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;">2. The Round of 32 = Maximum Chaos</h2>
        <p>
          104 matches. Yes, you heard that right. Instead of skipping straight from the groups to the Round of 16, we now have a Round of 32. This means third-place teams from the group stage can actually advance. Every single matchday 3 game is going to be an absolute bloodbath of teams trying to secure a top-3 finish. Goal differential will be the deciding factor of who goes home and who stays.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Anton', sans-serif;">3. RIP to Dead Rubber Matches</h2>
        <p>
          Because 8 of the best third-placed teams go through, literally no team is mathematically eliminated until the very last second. You won't see any "meaningless" group stage games where the managers just play the B-team. Everyone has to fight for their lives.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-pink-100 border-[3px] border-black shadow-[4px_4px_0px_#000]">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-2">TL;DR:</h3>
          <p class="font-bold">More teams = more Cinderella runs. Stop listening to the nostalgics on Twitter. The 48-team era is going to be the most chaotic and entertaining month of football we've ever witnessed. Period.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-between items-center border-t-[4px] border-black pt-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="font-anton text-xl uppercase text-black hover:text-pink-500 transition-colors">← Back to Guides</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
